---
import Guide from '../../layouts/Guide.astro';
import { stations, ZONE_NAMES } from '../../lib/data.js';

const hourlyStations = stations.filter((s) => s.hourly).sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
---

<Guide
  slug="hourly-booking"
  title="Hourly booking stations — 3-hour minimum retiring rooms"
  description="The Indian Railway stations that offer hourly retiring room bookings with a 3-hour minimum, ideal for short layovers."
  updated="2026-02-15"
>

<p>
  Standard retiring room slots are 12, 24, or 48 hours. But at select stations, IRCTC allows hourly bookings with
  a 3-hour minimum — useful for layovers, daytime rest stops between connecting trains, or shower-and-go pit stops.
</p>

<h2>How hourly booking works</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Minimum booking:</strong> 3 hours</li>
  <li><strong>Maximum hourly slot:</strong> 11 hours (beyond that, the 12-hour slot is cheaper)</li>
  <li><strong>Pricing:</strong> proportional to the 12-hour tariff, with a small premium per hour</li>
  <li><strong>Availability:</strong> only at stations that have explicitly enabled hourly booking in the IRCTC system</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Hourly slots are particularly common at stations with high transit volume — major junctions where passengers
  often have 4–10 hour waits between connecting trains.
</p>

<h2>When hourly beats the 12-hour slot</h2>
<p>
  The breakeven is typically around 7–8 hours. If you need the room for less than 7 hours, hourly booking saves
  money. Beyond that, the 12-hour slot is the better deal even if you don't use all the time.
</p>

<h2>Stations with hourly booking enabled</h2>
<p>
  Based on indexed data, the following {hourlyStations.length} stations currently offer hourly retiring room booking.
  Click any station for current tariffs and room types.
</p>

<div class="not-prose grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 my-8">
  {hourlyStations.map((s) => (
    <a href={`/stations/${s.slug}`} class="p-3 border border-rail-ink/10 bg-rail-chalk hover:border-rail-saffron rounded-sm no-underline transition-colors">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-rail-saffron2">{s.code}</p>
      <p class="font-display font-semibold text-rail-ink mt-0.5">{s.name}</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-rail-steel mt-0.5">{s.city} · {ZONE_NAMES[s.zone]}</p>
    </a>
  ))}
</div>

<h2>Note on availability</h2>
<p>
  Even at hourly-enabled stations, hourly slots are subject to room availability. During peak holiday and festival
  travel (Diwali, Holi, Chhath, Christmas–New Year, summer vacation), expect hourly inventory to be the first to
  sell out. Book as far in advance as possible.
</p>

</Guide>
